post_cb({"12139108": {"CommentCount": "0", "ViewCount": "316", "PostTypeId": "1", "LastEditorUserId": "2555451", "CreationDate": "2012-08-27T09:10:54.807", "LastActivityDate": "2015-01-22T18:40:32.000", "Title": "c++ floating point exception", "AcceptedAnswerId": "12139168", "LastEditDate": "2015-01-22T18:40:32.000", "Id": "12139108", "Score": "0", "Body": "<p>I did this for the Euler project problem 5, but for some reason I get a floating point exception:</p>\n<pre><code>#include &lt;iostream&gt;\nusing namespace std;\n\nint main ()\n{\n    long num;\n    bool isnum = false;\n    long i = 20;\n\n    while (isnum == false)\n    {\n        for (int j = 0; j &lt;= 20; j++)\n        {\n            if (i % j != 0)\n            {\n                break;\n            }\n            else\n            {\n                num = i;\n                isnum = true;\n            }\n        }\n        i+=20;\n    }\n    cout &lt;&lt; num &lt;&lt; endl;\n    return 0;\n}\n</code></pre>\n<p>What I don't understand is how there can be a floating point exception when I do nothing with my code that would output a non-integer number.</p>\n", "Tags": "<c++>", "OwnerUserId": "1627234", "AnswerCount": "3"}, "12139221": {"ParentId": "12139108", "CommentCount": "0", "Body": "<p>Since you use <code>i % j</code> with <code>j</code> being initialized to zero, you get undefined behavior, according to 5.6 [expr.mul] paragraph 4:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p id=\"so_12139108_12139221_0\">... If the second operand of / or % is zero the behavior is undefined. ...</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>This can yield, for example, a floating point exception. I can also cause nastier things to happen.</p>\n", "OwnerUserId": "1120273", "PostTypeId": "2", "Id": "12139221", "Score": "3", "CreationDate": "2012-08-27T09:18:15.503", "LastActivityDate": "2012-08-27T09:18:15.503"}, "bq_ids": {"n4140": {"so_12139108_12139221_0": {"section_id": 6106, "quality": 0.8, "length": 4}}, "n3337": {"so_12139108_12139221_0": {"section_id": 5872, "quality": 0.8, "length": 4}}, "n4659": {"so_12139108_12139221_0": {"section_id": 7603, "quality": 0.8, "length": 4}}}, "12139168": {"ParentId": "12139108", "CommentCount": "0", "Body": "<blockquote>\n<p id=\"so_12139108_12139168_0\">i % j</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>There's a division by zero here because j is initialized to 0.</p>\n", "OwnerUserId": "786962", "PostTypeId": "2", "Id": "12139168", "Score": "8", "CreationDate": "2012-08-27T09:14:35.103", "LastActivityDate": "2012-08-27T09:14:35.103"}, "12139172": {"ParentId": "12139108", "CommentCount": "0", "Body": "<p>You are doing <code>i % j</code> with j == 0 at the first iteration of the <code>for</code> loop.</p>\n<p>Thus the floating point exception.</p>\n", "OwnerUserId": "667433", "PostTypeId": "2", "Id": "12139172", "Score": "1", "CreationDate": "2012-08-27T09:14:59.003", "LastActivityDate": "2012-08-27T09:14:59.003"}});